Need Ideas in Current Markets? Energy Outperforms Again

This past week, S&P 500 Energy was up \(\sim 2.7\%\) , outperforming the SPX index by \(\sim 289\) bps (- 291bps/- 1,434bps YTD/LTM). Within the energy sub- sectors, US Refining was best performing and NAM Midstream worst (details within).

Weekly Best- Performing Energy Sub- Sector: US Refining (up \(\sim 4.4\%\) ); (+178bps vs XLE). DK was the sub- sector's best- performing stock (up \(\sim 12.1\%\) ); PSX was the worst- performing stock (up \(\sim 2.5\%\) ). Weekly Worst- Performing Energy Sub- Sector: NAM Midstream (up \(\sim 0.8\%\) ); (- 182bps vs XLE). PAA was the best- performing stock (up \(\sim 2.1\%\) ) for the sub- sector, PPL CN was the worst- performing stock (down \(\sim 1.2\%\) ). Weekly S&P 500 sectors: Energy best performing (up \(\sim 2.7\%\) ); Consumer Staples worst performing (down \(\sim 1.8\%\) ).
